==<span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">Description==

{{Blurimage|file=989.2.webp|width=250px|caption=A photograph of several houses in <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">Level '''989.3'''</span>.|hovertext=Paradise?}}{{Blurimage|file=OIP (17).jpg|width=250px|caption=A photograph of the interior of a <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''House'''</span> in <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Level 989.3'''</span>.|hovertext=Stay a while?}}Level 989.3 is a large complex of houses and miscellaneous structures, floating above a presumably infinite ocean. While at first it appears to be made up of a broad-ranging set of materials, closer inspection reveals that all non-organic surfaced in the level are constructed entirely from tiles of varying color, but the same uniform material. A wide variety of structures are present, the most common of these being <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Houses'''</span>. <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Houses'''</span> are uniquely non-Euclidean, with the interior space far larger than the exterior could accommodate under normal circumstances. The interiors of these <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Houses'''</span> widely vary, from deep swimming pools with floating inflatable furniture to tiled houses with furniture uniquely not made out of tiles. Another notable structure within the level is referred to as <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Arches'''</span>. This is a broad term for the square arches, serving seemingly no purpose, spread throughout the level. Due to the grayed colors and distinct lack of contrast, it is almost impossible to tell it is made out of tiles unless you feel it. <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Arches'''</span> are completely benign and no negative side effects have been traced to it. Another prevalent structure is the <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Pools'''</span>, salmon-colored tiled depressions at various points within the level filled with crystal clear water. The pools vary in temperature from 50°F to 100°F, while most hover at ~80°F. Excluding the presence of one particular entity which will be elaborated on later, these pools host no life and are entirely safe, even to drink. Natural plant life in the form of palm trees and small stretches of Kentucky Bluegrass dot the tile in small depressions filled with dirt. A third unique structure spread around the level is the <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Towers'''</span>. These <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Towers'''</span> manifest as roughly twelve-foot-tall tiled towers, typically with some form of lighting fixture at the junction between the roof and the walls. These towers can also be placed in close proximity with each other, in which case a bridge will form at the very top that reaches down four feet, or 1/3rd of the tower's total height. They are popular areas for sightseeing.

==Wildlife==
<tabber>
|-|Aquipuribacter-Clarifex=

<span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Aquipuribacter-Clarifex'''</span></span> is a somewhat legendary bacteria commonly found in bodies of water excluding the surrounding oceans. The bacteria feeds itself primarily off of dirt, non-natural contaminants and any diseases wanderers may bring into the level's waters. Through a series of biochemical processes, <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''A. Clarifex'''</span> purifies the water by somehow getting nutrients from these contaminants, which prevents illnesses contacted from drinking the water. It is unadvised to combine <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''A. Clarifex'''</span> with other water-adjacent liquids such as [[Object 1|Almond Water]], as it will 'purify' these substances as well, converting it into regular water.

<span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''A. Clarifex'''</span> is well-known for its fragility. It cannot survive in waters from outside the level, including bottled water, ice or re-liquefied steam. It cannot be taken outside the level for unknown reasons, simply staying in place and dropping back into the water upon exit. Other than here and [[Level 989|its parent level]], <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''A. Clarifex'''</span> is not found anywhere else.
|-|Plant Life=

Various forms of plant life exist within the level. The first and most noticeable are the palm trees, specifically <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Coconut Palms'''</span>. Cocos nucifera is a large palm, growing up to 30 metres (100 feet) tall, with pinnate leaves 4–6 m (13–20 ft) long, and pinnae 60–90 centimetres (2–3 ft) long; old leaves break away cleanly, leaving the trunk smooth. A critical difference between the variety found here and the varieties found elsewhere is that these plants are incapable of producing their signature coconuts, leaving only the tree itself. As such, <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Coconut Palms'''</span> here have been given the full title of <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Cocos nucifera ssp. nullacrescatii'''</span>. They are a source of shade and reportedly comfort, as those who stay near the trees for prolonged periods report a deep feeling of calmness. The second primary form is <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Kentucky Bluegrass'''</span>, which populates in small depressions in the tile, seemingly growing directly from the tiles themselves. The <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Kentucky Bluegrass'''</span> is indestructible, but the <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Coconut Palms'''</span> are not, allowing them to be harvested. The <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Coconut Palms'''</span> are surprisingly entirely edible with a tough texture, providing valuable nutrients and being a major source of food. If removed, <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Coconut Palms'''</span> will instantly regrow within 30 minutes, except if being directly looked at, in which the process will suddenly halt and not resume until one's gaze is averted.
|-|Aquatic Life=

Various types of fish and aquatic plant life are present within the level. Fish present have an extremely wide range, with the larger species of fish present reaching up to 218 pounds and the smallest reaching down to 30 milligrams. Multiple genera are represented in this broad range, from <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Salmo'''</span> to <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Mola'''</span> and from <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Notemigonus'''</span> to <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Callorhinchus'''</span>. Aquatic plant life mostly consists of several types of seaweeds, anomalously colored a bright pink, and coral reefs colored in several types of white and pink.
</tabber>

==Miscellaneous Information==

<span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Level 989.3'''</span> is believed to reside at the bottom of [[Level 989]] in a similar manner that [[Level 164]] is believed to reside at the bottom of [[The Void]]. This is evidenced by the presence of [[Level 989]]'s tower at the dead center of the level. In the ocean of the level, large floating magenta spheres are present on the horizon. Using telescopes it has been determined that these spheres are also made of tile. These spheres are an incredibly large distance away from the bulk of the level, rendering it almost impossible to reach. There has been one recorded case of someone reaching this area.
