The level's tiled landmass is roughly 800 square miles, comparable in size to Mauritius, a nation within [[The Frontrooms|the Frontrooms]]. Suspended in the ocean of <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Level 989.3'''</span>'s ocean's shallower zones are white sea platforms and small white towers peeking just above the water. These are popular places to go fish as they are relatively isolated from the rest of the community. <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Level 989.3'''</span> is in a constant, persistent state of sunset, with an orange glow always coming from this level's sun. However, in contrast the sky is a beautiful shade of purplish-magenta, described as calming to gaze upon. Uniquely, <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Level 989.3'''</span>'s sun does not hurt or inflict negative effects upon those who look at it, and even prolonged periods of gazing yield no negative results, instead instilling a calming feeling.
==Communities==
===Colony of Level 989.3===
Instead of several different colonies constantly at odds with each other, residents of <span style="font-family:Agency FB;background:linear-gradient(to right, mediumorchid, salmon); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">'''Level 989.3'''</span> have come to a unique agreement, in which one megacolony<ref>Not to be confused with [[Level 399#The Megacolony|The Megacolony]].</ref> would be the only present colony. While independent individuals and isolated researchers do exist, they often lead towards joining this megacolony. This megacolony currently has a total population of roughly 2,250 residents with a population density of ~2.8 people per square mile, typically ordinary people who arrived at this level from others, but also including researchers affiliated with a separate group but under the megacolony's common name. The colony itself does not have a core administration as many people live independently, but the colony does support small local administrations and core services such as maintenance and small hospitals, oftentimes staffed by the [[Backrooms Red Cross]] or local volunteers. Typically, members of this colony are open to trade, and membership is nonexistent, the only form of attendance is simply associating oneself with them; this can however be revoked if a large group opposes it.

==Entrances and Exits==
===Entrances===
*The primary entrance into this level is jumping off the tower of [[Level 989]], which may rarely lead here.
*Rarely, a similar entrance can be encountered by climbing down the tower of [[Level 989]] using the stairs.
*Very rarely<ref>While the painting's placement is permanent, only 6 circumstances have ever been recorded. Three have occurred in [[Level 37]], one has occurred in [[Level 7]], and two have occurred in [[Level 330]].</ref> in aquatic levels, a painting resembling the level may appear, interacting with it may send one here.
===Exits===
*Swimming out far enough may lead to [[Level 330]] or [[Level 100]].
*Locating the tower of [[Level 989]] and beginning to ascend it will cause one to black out and awaken at the typical starting point.
**Any exits performable in normal circumstances in [[Level 989]] can be performed here, as there is an entrance to [[Level 989#The Guts|The Guts]] located at floor level.
